  <p>During the World Cup, you will see odds everywhere — on sportsbook apps, in promotions, quoted by friends. Most explanations of how they work are written by sites trying to get you to bet more. This one is not. The purpose here is narrow and honest: to let you read a betting line accurately, understand what it is really telling you, and recognize the house edge baked into every number.</p>

  <p>If you understand odds properly, one conclusion becomes unavoidable: the odds are never a fair coin. They are a price, set by an operator that builds in a margin. Knowing that is the most useful thing this guide can give you.</p>

